<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1527] Factor out type checks in EmbedResultSet and EmbedPreparedStatement</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1527</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;EmbedPreparedStatement and EmbedResultSet have many occurrences of&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    switch (...) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        case Types.CHAR:
        case Types.VARCHAR:
        case Types.LONGVARCHAR:
        case Types.CLOB:
            break;
        default:
            throw dataTypeConversion(...);
    }

&lt;p&gt;and&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    switch (...) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        case Types.BINARY:
        case Types.VARBINARY:
        case Types.LONGVARBINARY:
        case Types.BLOB:
            break;
        default:
            throw dataTypeConversion(...);
    }

&lt;p&gt;Instead of having many copies of this code, it would be good to factor&lt;br/&gt;
it out into methods that can be shared. For instance, one could add&lt;br/&gt;
these methods to DataTypeDescriptor:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  public static boolean isAsciiStreamCompatible(int jdbcType)&lt;br/&gt;
  public static boolean isBinaryStreamCompatible(int jdbcType)&lt;br/&gt;
  public static boolean isCharacterStreamCompatible(int jdbcType)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
